The paper focuses on eye tracking and gaze behaviour analysis in the context of 360-degree videos, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspects. The paper also mentions the use of eye tracking in the assessment of subjective quality and mental load, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the development of a new annotation tool and a classification algorithm, which may involve graphics (cs.GR) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
